    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Presenting a museum-grade FD3S RX-7, a definitive example of 90s JDM engineering. This vehicle features the 13B-REW rotary engine with its sophisticated sequential twin-turbocharger system intact and functioning with factory precision. The power delivery is seamless, managed by a precise five-speed short-throw gearbox and a Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis remains uncompromising, utilizing its original lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension and 50/50 weight distribution for peerless cornering kinematics. This specimen is mechanically flawless, with a cooling system overhauled for longevity and apex seals showing optimal compression. No modifications, no defects\u2014just pure, high-revving performance in a concours-quality shell.",
      "price": 46500.0,
